sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Blue gR4mR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A gRNA targeting mRFP, negatively regulated by Blue Light Sensor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gRNA targeting mRFP is a no-BioBrick-scars assembly of the red light regulated promoter BBa_K592006 (PFixK2), DNA sequence of a gRNA that targets mRFP reporter and a reliable terminator BBa_B0015. This gRNA sequence comes from the following literature: QI, LEI S., LARSON, MATTHEW H., GILBERT, LUKE A., DOUDNA, JENNIFER A., WEISSMAN, JONATHAN S., ARKIN, ADAM P. & LIM, WENDELL A. 2013. Repurposing CRISPR as an RNA-Guided Platform for Sequence-Specific Control of Gene Expression. Cell, 152, 1173-1183.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hongyi WU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The gRNA sequence is de novo synthesized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: gRNA shall be exactly transcribed out. Any extra nucleotides would potentially jeopardize the normal function of the gRNA. Therefore, BioBrick scars are not allowed here. Instead of cut-and-ligation, overlap PCR is preferred for the assembly task (changing promoter). In addition, a reliable terminator is applied here to ensure the termination of gRNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: FixK2 promoter is the wild-type promoter to which phospho-FixJ binds. FixJ in turn can be regulated by YF1, the blue light-sensing protein. This promoter shows very little leaky activity in the absence of FixJ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: FixK2 promoter omes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence information was provided by Moffat (Moffat et al. 2009). The DNA was synthesized by GenScript.
